  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1ea17fbfcd7761ee8bc32f77efff4d0befcff1a7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.441ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {1} _{A}(x)=\left[\ x\in A\ \right].}"></span>
</p><p>For example, the <a href="/wiki/Dirichlet_function" title="Dirichlet function">Dirichlet function</a> is the indicator function of the <a href="/wiki/Rational_number" title="Rational number">rational numbers</a> as a subset of the <a href="/wiki/Real_number" title="Real number">real numbers</a>.
